oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Hogan, C.A., photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Cannon County land judging team placed first in the 4-H contest at the 4-H Club Camp in Cumberland County.

One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil Conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s.
Left to right: Albert Warren, coach; Ralph Davenport; Gayle Tate; Stephen Jernigan; John Hendrix of State Farmers Mutual Insurance Company presenting trophy.
